Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Bronx Shepherds been organized by pastors, ministers, and lay members who decided to remain in the South Bronx when many institutions left the area from over two decades ago. The group felt that the task of rebuilding the Bronx would be theirs. As they discussed approaches, goals, and objectives, they finally agreed that the organization's mission would be the rehabilitation of the physical, social, and economic conditions of the community in addition to providing spiritual influences and leadership. The Bronx Shepherds Restoration (BSR) has been providing much-needed services to Bronx residents since it was formed in 1980. Today, they have approximately 40 member churches, 99% of which are minority congregations. There are more than 10,000 members in the total constituency.
